      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I've looked at and experimented with the ARM tasks. Our ARM tasks run in an `arm_container`. https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/f3e35633690c71ebb69ec2ed08998565cade1522/.cirrus.yml#L190-L196\r\n\r\nThe [CirrusCI docs](https://cirrus-ci.org/guide/linux/#linux-containers) mention that `arm_container` tasks run on Graviton2 (ARM processor) instances in AWS via Kubernetes (`container` runs via Kubernetes in the Google Cloud). We can't use the macOS tasks as the tracepoints are Linux only..\r\n\r\nI'll look into converting an existing task into a VM.",
